  "_doc": "Phase-3d demo: DEMUX, DECODER, and ENCODER side by side. Click VERILOG in the bottom toolbar to see how each lowers:\n  • DEMUX 1:4 — every output is `(sel == k) ? data : 1'b0`, routing the single data input to one of four outputs.\n  • DECODER 2:4 — every output is `(addr == k)`, producing a one-hot bit vector from a 2-bit address.\n  • ENCODER 4:2 (priority) — nested ternary chain: highest active input wins, output is its index encoded in 2 bits.\nAll three are pure continuous assignments — no `always` blocks needed — and parse cleanly with iverilog.",
